ecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>So, my solution was to try and find something more rigid. Ideally, it would be easy enough to cut and modify, which excludes wood, but something still fairly insulating. I decided to try Recticel insulation foam, which is a rigid foam like substance that you can get from a department store. I found that it was pretty easy to make a cut with a box cutter and scissors. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!SbA0!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f8481c8-1a8b-48c3-a4ae-5c599c522874_4032x3024.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!SbA0!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f8481c8-1a8b-48c3-a4ae-5c599c522874_4032x3024.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!SbA0!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f8481c8-1a8b-48c3-a4ae-5c599c522874_4032x3024.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!SbA0!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4f8481c8-1a8b-48c3-a4ae-5c599c522874_4032x3024.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!SbA0!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.c